    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis for CFD hemolysis prediction (MRL 5)",
    "description": "A variance-based Sobol sensitivity analysis was performed over 2048 quasi-random samples (Saltelli sampling) varying inlet flow rate (3–7 L/min), impeller speed (2000–3500 RPM), blood viscosity (3.0–4.5 mPa·s), and power-law hemolysis model coefficients (C: 1.0e-6 to 3.4e-6, α: 0.765–0.810, β: 0.062–0.078). First-order and total-order Sobol indices were computed; impeller speed and hemolysis model coefficient C were identified as dominant factors, together accounting for 78% of output variance in the relative hemolysis index, with blood viscosity contributing a further 14% through interaction effects.",
    "method": "Variance-based Sobol (Saltelli 2010), 2048 quasi-random samples",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "impellerSpeed",
      "hemolysisModelCoefficientC",
      "bloodViscosity"
    ],
    "sampleSize": 2048
  },
