    "actor": "https://uofa.net/org/morrison-cfd-lab/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed at MRL 5 rigor. All 13 factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels (required Gradation 4; achieved Gradation 4 or 5 in all cases). Three independent validation results (hemolysis index, velocity field, mesh convergence) each include comparedAgainst, prov:wasGeneratedBy, and hasUncertaintyQuantification links with substantive UQ content. Global Sobol sensitivity analysis (n=2048) identifies dominant uncertainty sources (impeller speed, hemolysis model coefficient C) and confirms that combined prediction uncertainty is within the ±18% NIH acceptance band at 95% confidence. Operating envelope is concrete and bounded; applicability constraint defines in-scope patient population and geometry. No shortfalls in achieved vs. required levels; no offset rationale required. The model is credible for predicting absolute hemolysis levels for the Class II CPB device across the validated operating envelope and is accepted for regulatory submission.",
